## 05:00 Community News

### 05:15 MicroPython v1.27.0 Released

MicroPython v1.27.0 has been released and contains a wealth of upgrades \- [Release Notes](https://github.com/micropython/micropython/releases/tag/v1.27.0) and [Download](https://micropython.org/download/).

```
"This release of MicroPython adds support for ESP32-C5 and ESP32-P4 microcontrollers. The ESP32-P4 can work either standalone as a general purpose processor, or with an external wireless co-processor, currently either an ESP32-C5 or ESP32-C6. Board profiles are provided for all three of these configurations, as well as for the new ESP32-C5.

Support for the low-power and high performing STM32U5xx series is also added in this release, supporting USB, ADC, DAC, UART, I2C, SPI and RTC, with a board profile for the NUCLEO-U5A5ZJ-Q. Rigorous and ongoing hardware-based testing is an important part of MicroPython, and with the increasing number of supported hardware platforms -- along with a growing test suite -- it's important to make the tests run as smoothly and as automated as possible."
```

## 20:36 Status Updates

21:03 @foamyguy(host)

* Fixing a few issues that shook out from BitmapLabel changes and refactoring  
* MagTag Literature quotes clock guide  
* Made a displayio CheckBox widget  
* Working on holiday card maker for Fruit Jam. Input text for front/inside, and choose either to make a snowflake or use custom SVG or BMP for the front. It outputs a printable HTML file to CPSAVES

22:46 @danh

* AirLift wifi implementation:  
  * Making good progress. Connection to AP and all other non-socket operations, including host lookup and ping, are now working.  
  * Working on sockets now.  
  * NINA-FW has actually provided low-level socket operations starting a few years ago, but hardly anyone uses them except `BetterWiFiNINA`. Looking at whether it’s useful to use the new operations. There might be issues with SSL.

25:12 @tannewt

* PR out for Zephyr SPI support: [https://github.com/adafruit/circuitpython/pull/10752](https://github.com/adafruit/circuitpython/pull/10752)  
  * Merged zephyr\_i2c and zephyr\_serial back into busio. The Zephyr code will be responsible for delegating to port-specific code for dynamic creation.  
  * Zephyr SPI is working along with displayio.  
  * Add module enabling based on reverse dependencies so when `busio` is included, then `displayio` and friends are too.  
  * Added build tests around discovering flash and RAM in the Zephyr device tree.  
  * I want to test on more boards along with testing the SDCard support.  
* Prepping for \#CircuitPython2026
